        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 13 at 3:01PM MDT by NWS Pueblo CO</headline>
        <description>At 300 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Gleneagle, or 14 miles north of Colorado Springs, moving east at 20
mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Northern Colorado Springs, Monument, Air Force Academy, Black Forest,
Gleneagle, Falcon, and Cimarron Hills.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
